WorldStage Newsonline– ABC Transport Plc, a Nigerian firm that is into road passenger transportation between major cities in the south, north central and Abuja has released its  profit forecast for second quarter ending 30th June 2021 with projected turnover/revenue of N1.332 billion The company also projected a profit after tax N34.585 million for the Q2. Cash/bank balance at the beginning of the period is projected to be negative at N159.305 million while at the end of the period will remain in negative N106.871 million.